@NODE ABOUT "Intoduction"

Why did I wrote this program?

At first, I would only play with the new Reaction Gui and learned how to make use
of it in my programs. This was the beginning ...

I used Ghostscript from the Shell, and the usage was laborius. Commandlines over
two lines long (everyone who has used Ghostscript will know).

@ENDNODE 

@NODE VORAUSSETZUNGEN "system requirements"

What GhostscriptGUI V1.20 needs?

Hardware:
=========

- an Amiga :-)

- all requirements of Ghostscript




Software:
=========

- OS 3.0 and MUI 3.8 or OS 3.5
 
- a complete Ghostscript-Installation with assign Ghostscript:
- to print Turboprint V7 
- a PNG-Datatype to view a document



@ENDNODE

@NODE INSTALL "Installation of GhostscriptGUI V1.10

Copy the whole drawer where ever you want!!!


@ENDNODE

@NODE GHOST "Ghostscript?  What is that?"

What is Ghostscript?

Ghostscript is a Shell command to view or print PDF or PostScript Files.


Where to find Ghostscript?

- if you own Turboprint V7 , on disk 2

- Aminet: gfx/show

@ENDNODE

@NODE BEDIENUNG "The Usage of GhostscriptGUI"

Usage from the Shell:
---------------------

GhostscriptGUI FILE/K,GUI/K,VIEWER/K,PATH/K:

FILE/K:             Here you choose your file.
                    e.g.: GhostscriptGUI FILE=demo.ps
                          GhostscriptGUI demo.ps

                    GhostscriptGUI can be used as a default program (Icon of
                    the document).
                    VIEWER and GUI will be specified in the tooltypes
                    of the program icon (GhostscriptGUI.info).

GUI/K:              option: MUI or Reaction

                    If you specify nothing GsGUI will choose the GUI.

VIEWER/K:           Here you choose your viewer.
                    e.g.: cyberwindow, ...

                    default: multiview

PATH/K:             Here you specify your start path.


The GUI of GhostscriptGUI
-------------------------

PDF/PS-File:        choose here the file to view or print

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Page View

Resolution:         Choose here the resolution to view the file = size of the 
                    document.

                    Recomendation: 75 x 75 - 150 x 150

Colors:             Choose here the number of colors of the View image.

                    For the most PDF/PS-Documents Black and White is enough.

Slider Page:        Choose the Page to view.

Button Prev:        Click here to view the previous page.

Button Next:        Click here to view the next page.

Button View:        Click here to view the selected page.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Page Print 

Resolution:         Choose here the resolution to print.

Colors:             Choose here the number of colors to print.

                    Recomendation: The most PDF-Documents need only Black and White
                                   example: Datasheets of IC´s

Device:             With Turboprint everything should be OK!!!

                    Currently the Device "Workbench" does not print correctly.

                    Option: (-sDEVICE=amiga_printer)
                    On the printed pages are only the images not the text.

Print:              all Pages:           prints all pages             1,2,3,4, ...
                    only odd Pages:      prints only odd pages        1,3,5,7, ...
                    only even pages:     prints only even pages       2,4,6,8, ...

                    Recomendation:      First use "only odd Pages",
                                        then turn the stack, so that page 2
                                        will be printed on the back side of
                                        the first page and now select
                                        "only even Pages".

Startpage:          Choose here the first page to print.

Stoppage:           Choose here the last page to print.

                    If startpage>stoppage then nothing will be printed.

Print:              Starts the print process.  

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Page Convert

Destination:        Here you specify your destination file.
                    The correct ending (pdf/ps/png/pcx/iff) will be added.

Format:             Here you choose your output fileformat.
                    If you choose PNG/PCX/IFF, every page will be saved as
                    an own file.

                    e.g.: saa5246-011.png

Resolution:         Here you choose your destination resolution.

                    This chooser will only be relevant, if your format is PNG/PCX/IFF.

Colors:             Here you choose the number of colors.

                    This chooser will only be relevant, if your format is PNG/PCX/IFF.

Ghostscript Direct: If you set this checkmark, the convertion will be done directly 
                    from ghostscript.

                    Startpage/Stoppage will be ignored.

                    If GUI=MUI here is a chooser with yes/no.

                    This option is usefull, if on PS-Files there is only the first page
                    to display.

Startpage:          Here you choose your startpage.

Stoppage:           Here you choose your stoppage.

Convert:            The convertion will be started.

 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Tooltypes:

VIEWER/K:           Here you can choose your viewer.
                    e.g.: Multiview, Cyberwindow, ...
                    If you leave this option, default will be multiview.

PATH/K:             Here you can enter the path to your PDF/PS-Files.
                    e.g.: Data:PDF/

GUI/K:              Here you choose your GUI:   - Reaction
                                                - MUI

                    If you leave this option, GsGUI will choose it for you.

                    Recomendation: Reaction

FILE/K:             Here you choose your file.
@ENDNODE

